    {
      "id": "cf5c10be-2ab8-469f-8a3e-9a8a1a479340",
      "type": "markdown",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": "## 2. How a decision is made\n\nA policy is just **data**. The verdict is deterministic C# - same input, same answer, every time, with a matched rule and reason.",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "mimeType": "text/html",
          "content": "\u003Ch2 id=\u0022how-a-decision-is-made\u0022\u003E2. How a decision is made\u003C/h2\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EA policy is just \u003Cstrong\u003Edata\u003C/strong\u003E. The verdict is deterministic C# - same input, same answer, every time, with a matched rule and reason.\u003C/p\u003E\n"
        }
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "2517cbad-ec12-4192-85df-85b433292ec6",
      "type": "code",
      "language": "csharp",
      "source": "DemoUi.Banner(\u0022How a decision is made\u0022, \u0022Policy is YAML. The verdict is deterministic C#.\u0022, \u0022The model proposes a tool call; the runtime checks it before execution.\u0022);\n\nvar decisionYaml = \u0022\u0022\u0022\napiVersion: governance.toolkit/v1\nversion: \u00221.0\u0022\nname: reporting-agent\ndefault_action: deny\nrules:\n  - name: allow-balance\n    condition: \u0022tool_name == \u0027get_balance\u0027\u0022\n    action: allow\n    priority: 10\n  - name: allow-transactions\n    condition: \u0022tool_name == \u0027list_transactions\u0027\u0022\n    action: allow\n    priority: 10\n\u0022\u0022\u0022;\n\nvar decisionKernel = new GovernanceKernel();\ndecisionKernel.LoadPolicyFromYaml(decisionYaml);\nvar decisionRows = new List\u003C(string Label, string Value)\u003E();\nforeach (var toolName in new[] { \u0022get_balance\u0022, \u0022transfer_funds\u0022 })\n{\n    var result = decisionKernel.EvaluateToolCall(\u0022did:mesh:contoso-reporter\u0022, toolName, new Dictionary\u003Cstring, object\u003E());\n    decisionRows.Add((toolName, result.Allowed ? $\u0022ALLOW - {result.PolicyDecision?.MatchedRule}\u0022 : $\u0022DENY - {result.Reason}\u0022));\n}\n\nDemoUi.Table(decisionRows, \u0022Same policy, explainable outcomes\u0022);\nDemoUi.Verdict(decisionRows[0].Value.StartsWith(\u0022ALLOW\u0022) \u0026\u0026 decisionRows[1].Value.StartsWith(\u0022DENY\u0022), \u0022A prompt-injected reporting agent still cannot move money.\u0022);",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "mimeType": "text/html",
          "content": "\u003Cdiv style=\u0027font-family:Segoe UI,system-ui,sans-serif;background:#10243f;border-left:6px solid #25c2a0;padding:18px 22px;margin:14px 0;color:#f4f8ff\u0027\u003E\u003Cdiv style=\u0027font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#69dcc5\u0027\u003EHow a decision is made\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cdiv style=\u0027font-size:22px;font-weight:700;margin-top:4px\u0027\u003EPolicy is YAML. The verdict is deterministic C#.\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cdiv style=\u0027font-size:14px;color:#bfd0e6;margin-top:6px\u0027\u003EThe model proposes a tool call; the runtime checks it before execution.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E"
        },
        {
          "mimeType": "text/html",
          "content": "\u003Ctable style=\u0027border-collapse:collapse;font:13.5px Segoe UI;background:#10243f;margin:8px 0\u0027\u003E\u003Ccaption style=\u0027text-align:left;color:#69dcc5;font-weight:700;padding:7px 12px\u0027\u003ESame policy, explainable outcomes\u003C/caption\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;color:#bfd0e6\u0027\u003Eget_balance\u003C/td\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;font-weight:700;color:#f4f8ff\u0027\u003EALLOW - allow-balance\u003C/td\u003E\u003C/tr\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;color:#bfd0e6\u0027\u003Etransfer_funds\u003C/td\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;font-weight:700;color:#f4f8ff\u0027\u003EDENY - No matching rules; default action is deny.\u003C/td\u003E\u003C/tr\u003E\u003C/table\u003E"
