    {
      "id": "45851474-8c4c-4e23-a001-ffc37c232b53",
      "type": "markdown",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": "## 3. Sub-millisecond enforcement\n\nGovernance only works if it is cheap enough to run on **every** action. The next cell measures 10,000 real evaluations live.",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "mimeType": "text/html",
          "content": "\u003Ch2 id=\u0022sub-millisecond-enforcement\u0022\u003E3. Sub-millisecond enforcement\u003C/h2\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EGovernance only works if it is cheap enough to run on \u003Cstrong\u003Eevery\u003C/strong\u003E action. The next cell measures 10,000 real evaluations live.\u003C/p\u003E\n"
        }
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "ba0e7389-86db-4200-b0d7-526f262a76b4",
      "type": "code",
      "language": "csharp",
      "source": "DemoUi.Banner(\u0022Sub-millisecond enforcement\u0022, \u0022An LLM call takes hundreds of milliseconds. Governance takes microseconds.\u0022, \u0022Ten policy rules, 10,000 real evaluations, measured live in this C# process.\u0022);\n\nvar benchmarkYaml = \u0022\u0022\u0022\napiVersion: governance.toolkit/v1\nversion: \u00221.0\u0022\nname: benchmark-policy\ndefault_action: allow\nrules:\n  - { name: block-delete, condition: \u0022tool_name == \u0027delete_file\u0027\u0022, action: deny, priority: 100 }\n  - { name: block-shell, condition: \u0022tool_name == \u0027shell_exec\u0027\u0022, action: deny, priority: 100 }\n  - { name: block-code, condition: \u0022tool_name == \u0027execute_code\u0027\u0022, action: deny, priority: 100 }\n  - { name: block-drop, condition: \u0022tool_name == \u0027drop_table\u0027\u0022, action: deny, priority: 100 }\n  - { name: block-transfer, condition: \u0022tool_name == \u0027transfer_funds\u0027\u0022, action: deny, priority: 100 }\n  - { name: block-exfiltrate, condition: \u0022tool_name == \u0027exfiltrate\u0027\u0022, action: deny, priority: 100 }\n  - { name: block-ssh, condition: \u0022tool_name == \u0027ssh_connect\u0027\u0022, action: deny, priority: 100 }\n  - { name: block-binary, condition: \u0022tool_name == \u0027run_binary\u0027\u0022, action: deny, priority: 100 }\n  - { name: block-fork-bomb, condition: \u0022tool_name == \u0027fork_bomb\u0027\u0022, action: deny, priority: 100 }\n  - { name: block-pii, condition: \u0022contains_pii == true\u0022, action: deny, priority: 90 }\n\u0022\u0022\u0022;\n\nvar benchmarkKernel = new GovernanceKernel(new GovernanceOptions { EnableAudit = false, EnableMetrics = false });\nbenchmarkKernel.LoadPolicyFromYaml(benchmarkYaml);\nvar allowArgs = new Dictionary\u003Cstring, object\u003E { [\u0022contains_pii\u0022] = false };\nvar denyArgs = new Dictionary\u003Cstring, object\u003E { [\u0022contains_pii\u0022] = false };\nfor (var warmup = 0; warmup \u003C 500; warmup\u002B\u002B)\n    _ = benchmarkKernel.EvaluateToolCall(\u0022did:mesh:contoso-teller\u0022, \u0022get_balance\u0022, allowArgs);\n\nconst int evaluationCount = 10_000;\nvar latencyTicks = new long[evaluationCount];\nvar wallTimer = Stopwatch.StartNew();\nfor (var index = 0; index \u003C evaluationCount; index\u002B\u002B)\n{\n    var started = Stopwatch.GetTimestamp();\n    _ = benchmarkKernel.EvaluateToolCall(\u0022did:mesh:contoso-teller\u0022, index % 2 == 0 ? \u0022shell_exec\u0022 : \u0022get_balance\u0022, index % 2 == 0 ? denyArgs : allowArgs);\n    latencyTicks[index] = Stopwatch.GetTimestamp() - started;\n}\nwallTimer.Stop();\nArray.Sort(latencyTicks);\n\ndouble ToMicroseconds(long ticks) =\u003E ticks * 1_000_000.0 / Stopwatch.Frequency;\nvar benchmarkP50 = ToMicroseconds(latencyTicks[(int)(evaluationCount * 0.50)]);\nvar benchmarkP95 = ToMicroseconds(latencyTicks[(int)(evaluationCount * 0.95)]);\nvar benchmarkP99 = ToMicroseconds(latencyTicks[(int)(evaluationCount * 0.99)]);\nvar benchmarkThroughput = evaluationCount / wallTimer.Elapsed.TotalSeconds;\n\nDemoUi.Table(new[]\n{\n    (\u0022Evaluations\u0022, $\u0022{evaluationCount:N0}\u0022),\n    (\u0022Wall-clock time\u0022, $\u0022{wallTimer.Elapsed.TotalMilliseconds:N0} ms\u0022),\n    (\u0022Throughput\u0022, $\u0022{benchmarkThroughput:N0} evaluations / second\u0022),\n    (\u0022Latency p50\u0022, $\u0022{benchmarkP50:F2} microseconds\u0022),\n    (\u0022Latency p95\u0022, $\u0022{benchmarkP95:F2} microseconds\u0022),\n    (\u0022Latency p99\u0022, $\u0022{benchmarkP99:F2} microseconds\u0022)\n}, \u0022Live result\u0022);\nConsole.WriteLine($\u0022At p50, governance adds about {benchmarkP50 / 1000.0 / 800.0 * 100.0:F4}% to an 800 ms model call.\u0022);",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "mimeType": "text/html",
          "content": "\u003Cdiv style=\u0027font-family:Segoe UI,system-ui,sans-serif;background:#10243f;border-left:6px solid #25c2a0;padding:18px 22px;margin:14px 0;color:#f4f8ff\u0027\u003E\u003Cdiv style=\u0027font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#69dcc5\u0027\u003ESub-millisecond enforcement\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cdiv style=\u0027font-size:22px;font-weight:700;margin-top:4px\u0027\u003EAn LLM call takes hundreds of milliseconds. Governance takes microseconds.\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cdiv style=\u0027font-size:14px;color:#bfd0e6;margin-top:6px\u0027\u003ETen policy rules, 10,000 real evaluations, measured live in this C# process.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E"
        },
        {
          "mimeType": "text/html",
          "content": "\u003Ctable style=\u0027border-collapse:collapse;font:13.5px Segoe UI;background:#10243f;margin:8px 0\u0027\u003E\u003Ccaption style=\u0027text-align:left;color:#69dcc5;font-weight:700;padding:7px 12px\u0027\u003ELive result\u003C/caption\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;color:#bfd0e6\u0027\u003EEvaluations\u003C/td\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;font-weight:700;color:#f4f8ff\u0027\u003E10,000\u003C/td\u003E\u003C/tr\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;color:#bfd0e6\u0027\u003EWall-clock time\u003C/td\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;font-weight:700;color:#f4f8ff\u0027\u003E379 ms\u003C/td\u003E\u003C/tr\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;color:#bfd0e6\u0027\u003EThroughput\u003C/td\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;font-weight:700;color:#f4f8ff\u0027\u003E26,354 evaluations / second\u003C/td\u003E\u003C/tr\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;color:#bfd0e6\u0027\u003ELatency p50\u003C/td\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;font-weight:700;color:#f4f8ff\u0027\u003E28.20 microseconds\u003C/td\u003E\u003C/tr\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;color:#bfd0e6\u0027\u003ELatency p95\u003C/td\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;font-weight:700;color:#f4f8ff\u0027\u003E51.50 microseconds\u003C/td\u003E\u003C/tr\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;color:#bfd0e6\u0027\u003ELatency p99\u003C/td\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;font-weight:700;color:#f4f8ff\u0027\u003E100.30 microseconds\u003C/td\u003E\u003C/tr\u003E\u003C/table\u003E"
        },
        {
          "mimeType": "text/plain",
          "content": "At p50, governance adds about 0.0035% to an 800 ms model call.\r\n"
        }
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "language": "csharp"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "df1c2f0e-1a4c-474c-b4c3-201b8384cbae",
      "type": "markdown",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": "## 4. Zero-trust: every action is checked\n\nThe LLM proposes a tool and arguments. The C# runtime owns execution and places the same AGT gate in front of every action.",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "mimeType": "text/html",
          "content": "\u003Ch2 id=\u0022zero-trust-every-action-is-checked\u0022\u003E4. Zero-trust: every action is checked\u003C/h2\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EThe LLM proposes a tool and arguments. The C# runtime owns execution and places the same AGT gate in front of every action.\u003C/p\u003E\n"
        }
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "6cc4dec1-84f3-4bd8-a143-3de848c8a02c",
      "type": "code",
      "language": "csharp",
      "source": "DemoUi.Banner(\u0022Zero-trust tool calls\u0022, \u0022The model proposes. The governed runtime disposes.\u0022, \u0022Safe calls execute; forbidden calls stop at the boundary with a reason.\u0022);\n\nvar tellerYaml = \u0022\u0022\u0022\napiVersion: governance.toolkit/v1\nversion: \u00221.0\u0022\nname: bank-teller-agent\ndefault_action: deny\nrules:\n  - { name: allow-balance, condition: \u0022tool_name == \u0027get_balance\u0027\u0022, action: allow, priority: 10 }\n  - { name: allow-transactions, condition: \u0022tool_name == \u0027list_transactions\u0027\u0022, action: allow, priority: 10 }\n  - { name: allow-ticket, condition: \u0022tool_name == \u0027open_ticket\u0027\u0022, action: allow, priority: 10 }\n\u0022\u0022\u0022;\n\nvar tellerKernel = new GovernanceKernel();\ntellerKernel.LoadPolicyFromYaml(tellerYaml);\nvar tellerCalls = new[]\n{\n    (Tool: \u0022get_balance\u0022, Args: new Dictionary\u003Cstring, object\u003E { [\u0022account\u0022] = \u0022L-7791\u0022 }),\n    (Tool: \u0022list_transactions\u0022, Args: new Dictionary\u003Cstring, object\u003E { [\u0022account\u0022] = \u0022L-7791\u0022 }),\n    (Tool: \u0022transfer_funds\u0022, Args: new Dictionary\u003Cstring, object\u003E { [\u0022amount\u0022] = 50_000, [\u0022to\u0022] = \u0022external\u0022 }),\n    (Tool: \u0022shell_exec\u0022, Args: new Dictionary\u003Cstring, object\u003E { [\u0022command\u0022] = \u0022rm -rf /\u0022 }),\n    (Tool: \u0022open_ticket\u0022, Args: new Dictionary\u003Cstring, object\u003E { [\u0022subject\u0022] = \u0022card lost\u0022 })\n};\n\nvar tellerRows = new List\u003C(string Label, string Value)\u003E();\nvar tellerAllowed = 0;\nforeach (var call in tellerCalls)\n{\n    var result = tellerKernel.EvaluateToolCall(\u0022did:mesh:contoso-teller\u0022, call.Tool, call.Args);\n    if (result.Allowed) tellerAllowed\u002B\u002B;\n    tellerRows.Add((call.Tool, result.Allowed ? \u0022ALLOW - execution may continue\u0022 : $\u0022BLOCK - {result.Reason}\u0022));\n}\n\nDemoUi.Table(tellerRows, $\u0022{tellerAllowed} allowed | {tellerCalls.Length - tellerAllowed} blocked | violations executed: 0\u0022);\nDemoUi.Verdict(tellerAllowed == 3, \u0022Forbidden calls were rejected before any tool implementation ran.\u0022);",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "mimeType": "text/html",
          "content": "\u003Cdiv style=\u0027font-family:Segoe UI,system-ui,sans-serif;background:#10243f;border-left:6px solid #25c2a0;padding:18px 22px;margin:14px 0;color:#f4f8ff\u0027\u003E\u003Cdiv style=\u0027font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#69dcc5\u0027\u003EZero-trust tool calls\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cdiv style=\u0027font-size:22px;font-weight:700;margin-top:4px\u0027\u003EThe model proposes. The governed runtime disposes.\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cdiv style=\u0027font-size:14px;color:#bfd0e6;margin-top:6px\u0027\u003ESafe calls execute; forbidden calls stop at the boundary with a reason.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E"
        },
        {
          "mimeType": "text/html",
          "content": "\u003Ctable style=\u0027border-collapse:collapse;font:13.5px Segoe UI;background:#10243f;margin:8px 0\u0027\u003E\u003Ccaption style=\u0027text-align:left;color:#69dcc5;font-weight:700;padding:7px 12px\u0027\u003E3 allowed | 2 blocked | violations executed: 0\u003C/caption\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;color:#bfd0e6\u0027\u003Eget_balance\u003C/td\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;font-weight:700;color:#f4f8ff\u0027\u003EALLOW - execution may continue\u003C/td\u003E\u003C/tr\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;color:#bfd0e6\u0027\u003Elist_transactions\u003C/td\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;font-weight:700;color:#f4f8ff\u0027\u003EALLOW - execution may continue\u003C/td\u003E\u003C/tr\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;color:#bfd0e6\u0027\u003Etransfer_funds\u003C/td\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;font-weight:700;color:#f4f8ff\u0027\u003EBLOCK - No matching rules; default action is deny.\u003C/td\u003E\u003C/tr\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;color:#bfd0e6\u0027\u003Eshell_exec\u003C/td\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;font-weight:700;color:#f4f8ff\u0027\u003EBLOCK - No matching rules; default action is deny.\u003C/td\u003E\u003C/tr\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;color:#bfd0e6\u0027\u003Eopen_ticket\u003C/td\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0027padding:6px 12px;font-weight:700;color:#f4f8ff\u0027\u003EALLOW - execution may continue\u003C/td\u003E\u003C/tr\u003E\u003C/table\u003E"
        },
        {
          "mimeType": "text/html",
          "content": "\u003Cdiv style=\u0027font-family:Segoe UI;background:#10243f;border-left:6px solid #25c2a0;padding:11px 14px;margin:8px 0;color:#f4f8ff\u0027\u003E\u003Cb style=\u0027color:#25c2a0\u0027\u003EDEFENDED\u003C/b\u003E - Forbidden calls were rejected before any tool implementation ran.\u003C/div\u003E"
        }
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "language": "csharp"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "57dcda12-f827-45ca-9de9-ee6c4c114b18",
      "type": "markdown",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": "## Recap\n\nIn five minutes, using the real .NET toolkit:\n\n- The runtime preflight exercised **eight governance controls**.\n- A **policy is data**; the decision is deterministic and explainable.\n- Enforcement costs **microseconds**, so it can guard every action.\n- One **runtime gate** governs every tool call; denied actions never reach execution.\n\n\u003E **The model proposes. The governed .NET runtime decides whether execution is allowed.**",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "mimeType": "text/html",
          "content": "\u003Ch2 id=\u0022recap\u0022\u003ERecap\u003C/h2\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EIn five minutes, using the real .NET toolkit:\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003EThe runtime preflight exercised \u003Cstrong\u003Eeight governance controls\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Epolicy is data\u003C/strong\u003E; the decision is deterministic and explainable.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003EEnforcement costs \u003Cstrong\u003Emicroseconds\u003C/strong\u003E, so it can guard every action.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003EOne \u003Cstrong\u003Eruntime gate\u003C/strong\u003E governs every tool call; denied actions never reach execution.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe model proposes. The governed .NET runtime decides whether execution is allowed.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n"
        }
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown"
      }
    }
  ],
